"n.肩章，肩饰 【英】 n. 肩章，肩饰 (a shoulder ornament for certain uniforms) 【考】 epaulet : shoulder / ring : finger(肩章戴在肩膀上/戒 指戴在手指上) n. (军服上有流苏的)肩章; 肩饰 【记】epau读: 挨炮, let让: 向我开炮! 我是人民解放军－肩章e出, pau读: 跑, let让: 让你出去跑100圈, 因为他的肩章上的星星多, 你不服不行. 【类】epaulet: shoulder = ring: finger 肩章戴在肩膀上 = 戒指戴在手指上 【记】pau 音：袍 + let 小东西；肩上(身上)披的袍子上装饰的小东西(星或者条或者块)→肩章；音：袍勒，袍子上勒的小东西 epaulet (n.)  1783, from French épaulette (16c.), diminutive of épaule ""shoulder,"" from Old French espaule (12c.), from Latin spatula ""flat piece of wood, splint,"" later ""shoulder blade,"" diminutive of spatha ""broad wooden instrument, broad sword,"" from Greek spathe ""a broad flat sword"" (see spade (n.1))."
